  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Considering the Tech Stack**\n\nI\'m currently evaluating the implications of React 19 and Express dependencies within a module-based project. The user\'s prompt is unclear about full-stack versus client-side, but the framework guidelines favor a full-stack approach with server-side API routes. I\'m leaning toward this default architecture.\n\n\n**Prioritizing Security and Architecture**\n\nI\'ve determined that a full-stack architecture (Express + Vite) is mandatory, given the use of the Gemini API for coral name generation. This choice is critical to protect the API key. Server-side Excel generation seems like the best approach due to its robustness. I\'m exploring server-side exceljs, to avoid client-side file system burdens, and also to reduce client-side libraries.\n\n\n**Refining Image Processing Flow**\n\nI\'m now focusing on how to handle image uploads and integrate the Gemini API for coral analysis. The server receives images (potentially base64 or multipart) and processes them. I will use the Gemini API (specifically `gemini-3.5-flash`) to generate: common/scientific names, descriptions, care levels, and growth details. The images are already available on the server, so generating the spreadsheet will be straightforward.\n\n\n"
