    thinking: "**Designing the Server File**\n\nI\'m now fully immersed in designing `/server.ts`. Currently, I\'m verifying and finalizing all necessary imports, specifically focusing on `express`, `path`, `vite`, and the `@google/genai` library, paying close attention to the `GoogleGenAI` class and its parameters.\n\n\n**Defining Server Features**\n\nI\'ve outlined the essential features for the server. The plan involves initializing `GoogleGenAI` and establishing routes. The `/api/generate-coral-names` route will handle concurrent Gemini 3.5 Flash calls for image analysis, utilizing `Promise.all` for efficiency and error handling for each image. Additionally, the `/api/export-excel` route will generate and send Excel files, handling coral data efficiently.\n\n\n**Verifying Gemini Schema**\n\nI\'m now focusing on defining the response schema for Gemini, specifically checking the properties for generating coral names. I\'ve confirmed the `Type` import from `@google/genai` is correct. The schema will define a JSON object with properties like `commonName`, `scientificName`, and others, all of which are strings, and it includes a `required` array. This all will inform the use of the Gemini 3.5 Flash model.\n\n\n**Implementing Lazy Initialization**\n\nI\'m now implementing lazy initialization for the Gemini client to avoid startup crashes if the API key is missing. This involves a helper function, `getGeminiClient`, which will initialize the `GoogleGenAI` client only when it is first needed within the route handlers. This way, the server won\'t crash on boot if the key is not present, and provides a clear message to the user.\n\n\n**Confirming Vite Configuration**\n\nI\'m now verifying the Vite configuration within `/server.ts`. I\'ve confirmed both development and production setups. During development, the Vite middleware is set up using `createViteServer`, while in production, it\'ll serve static assets from the `dist` directory, including an `index.html` file for any unmatched routes. The `createServer` import is now correctly handled.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I will create the backend `server.ts` file. It will set up the Express app, integrate the Vite middleware (for development vs production), implement lazy-loading for the Gemini SDK, analyze uploaded coral photos in parallel using `gemini-3.5-flash` with a strict JSON response schema, and provide an endpoint that builds and streams a styled Excel spreadsheet using `exceljs` with the coral details and embedded high-resolution photos."
