    thinking: "**Defining Visual Harmony**\n\nI\'ve made progress on outlining the visual design. I have extracted and listed some key design tokens: the page background color (`#FAF8F5`, mapped to `bg-natural-bg` in `src/index.css`) and the main text color (`#3D3B38`). I am confident that these are a great start!\n\n\n**Expanding the Color Palette**\n\nI\'m now expanding the color palette, noting specific hex codes for muted text (`#8E8A84`), accent orange (`#D9826C`), and sea green (`#4A7C7A`). I\'ve also defined border colors (`#E5E0D8`), an off-white panel color (`#FCFAF7`), and a white card color. Furthermore, I have also defined the rounded corners and the serif font! I\'m planning to style \"CoralNomad\" or \"Coral Cataloguer\" beautifully. Next, I\'ll update `/src/App.tsx`.\n\n\n**Refining the Naturalist Theme**\n\nI\'m now focusing on replacing the existing return statement with a naturalist theme. I\'ve pinpointed the relevant block of code, starting from line 223, and have identified the current background and text color classes. The page container will now use `bg-natural-bg` and `text-natural-text`, drawing from my recently defined color palette. I will also incorporate the serif font and rounded corners as I implement this replacement.\n\n\n**Implementing Glow Elements**\n\nI\'m now integrating soft, cream-colored glows to replace the cyber-tech aesthetic, thinking about how these will impact the visual feel. I\'m also styling the header for a refined naturalist look, incorporating a subtle border, blur, and sticky positioning. I am also working on the brand elements for the header. The header\'s icon will have a natural accent background, with the title using the defined serif font. Furthermore, I am working on the button, and badges UI elements too.\n\n\n**Defining UI Elements**\n\nI\'m now focusing on specific UI elements like the step indicator, drag-and-drop box, and bullet points. I\'m assigning classes for a green indicator (`bg-natural-teal`), step badges (`bg-natural-teal/10`), step titles (`text-3xl`), and step descriptions. I\'m also styling bullet points with icons, titles, and descriptions, and specifying class names for the drag-and-drop box with active and hover states. I am building the structure, and I\'ll keep refining the details!\n\n\n**Styling UI Components**\n\nI\'m now styling the UI components for the drag-and-drop section. I\'ve defined classes for the drag-drop title, subtitle, and browse text. I\'ve styled the pending upload list container, files grid item, delete action, submit bar container, and run button. I\'m focusing on their visual states, defining hover and disabled states for interactive elements. I\'m aiming for a cohesive and user-friendly interface.\n\n\n**Defining Loading Indicators**\n\nI\'m now focusing on the loading modal. I\'ve defined classes for the overlay, card, a pulsing accent bar, and the spinner, ensuring a soft, naturalist aesthetic with teal and cream hues. I\'ve also incorporated a serif font for the title and am using a semi-transparent background.\n\n\\n\\n\n\nI\'m now styling Step 2\'s components. I have defined classes for the header panel with shadow, border, and white background, including the grid for stats cards, and the individual coral cards with rounded borders, a white background and a naturalist border. I am styling both stats values.\n\n\n**Refining Component Styles**\n\nI\'m now refining the style of form elements for Step 2. I\'ve defined specific classes for photo boxes (`aspect-video`, rounded borders, border) and input fields (`w-full`, rounded corners, border, focus states with teal). The select fields are also styled with similar attributes, including cursor styles. Textarea fields have a relaxed leading, and resize handles. I\'ve also added exclude button styles!\n\n\n**Styling the Download Bar**\n\nI\'m now styling the bottom download bar and have defined classes for its container, the clear/start over button, and the download button, giving them rounded borders, appropriate background colors (including white and the accent color), padding, and hover states, as well as the important disabled states. I\'ve focused on ensuring a consistent, naturalist aesthetic, paying special attention to shadow and border styles for a clean, professional look. I am also reviewing the entire App.tsx return statement for a comprehensive update.\n\n\n"
